page.content: introduce grazing animals to keep the scrub down. Woodpeckers, Pigeons and Magpies live in oak trees.Blue Tits,Great Tits and Thrushes live in the scrub. Butterflies,bees and other insects live on the plains.Newts, frogs, toads and grass snakes live on the wetlands. There are 447 acres of common land and the great interest of the common is its variety of birds.The local people bought it for Â£1,250 in 1923.There are 500 species of flowers on the common.Here is a list of animals on the common: grey squirrel, stoats, rabbits, weasels, roe deer, field mice, harvest mice, rats, hedgehogs and voles.
